HEADWORD: Tripoli
<hw>Trip"o*li</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An
earthy substance originally brought from Tripoli, used in polishing
stones and metals. It consists almost wholly of the siliceous shells of
diatoms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tripoline</ent>⟦br⟧
